+    <p><b>Economy:</b> villagers gather wood, food, and gold and return them to your Town Center — or to a Mill, Lumber Camp, or Mining Camp built near the resource to cut walking time. Select villagers and use the Gather buttons to put them to work fast. Train more villagers there. Build Farms when berries run out, and Houses to raise your population cap.</p>
     <p><b>Military:</b> build a Barracks for swordsmen. Advance ages at the Town Center to unlock the Archery Range, Stable, and Siege Workshop — and stronger troops.</p>
     <p><b>Camera:</b> W A S D / arrows / screen edge to pan, mouse wheel to zoom, Q and E to rotate, middle-drag to pan. Click the minimap to jump.</p>
     <p><b>Keys:</b> S stop (with units selected) · F2 select all soldiers · <b>.</b> cycle idle villagers · Esc cancel/deselect · H help · M sound.</p>
+<p><b>Rally:</b> select a building and right-click the ground to set where new units go — rally your Town Center onto a resource and fresh villagers start gathering it immediately.</p>
 <p><b>Scores:</b> hold Tab for the live scorecard.</p>
 <p><b>Groups:</b> Shift+1–9 assigns selected units to a group, 1–9 recalls it, double-tap the digit to jump the camera there.</p>
